 "description": "`#[feature(type_alias_impl_trait)]`"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2023-06-03T01:03:48Z", "updated_at": "2023-06-03T01:03:50Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This is allowed:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntype Tait = impl Sized;\r\nfn foo() -> Tait {\r\n    42\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this is not: [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=8c5c645646c43fdfd0bec95f4653c6e2)\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntype Tait = impl Sized;\r\nfn foo() -> Tait {\r\n    loop{}\r\n    42\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: unconstrained opaque type\r\n --> src/lib.rs:3:13\r\n  |\r\n3 | type Tait = impl Sized;\r\n  |             ^^^^^^^^^^\r\n  |\r\n  = note: `Tait` must be used in combination with a concrete type within the same module\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt feels somewhat surprising to me, since unreachable code should still be typechecked. \r\n\r\n@rustbot label F-type_alias_impl_trait\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/112230/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/112230/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}